 Mt Ayliff - Police in Mt Ayliff have appealed to the public to assist them with information that help them locate a missing 17-year-old girl, Amahle Mjaca, from Lugelweni Loc, in Mt Ayliff. "On 28/12/2018 Amahle Mjaca went to Mt Ayliff town, and she has never returned back home," said police spokesperson, Capt Raphael Motloung. "Before she went missing, she was wearing a short white dress. "She’s light or fair in complexion." Capt Motloung said that anyone, who can assist in finding her or has seen her can contact Capt Ngcobo of MT Ayliff SAPS on 0739856202\0725241329 or alternatively the Crime Stop number 0860010111. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 